<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/images/favicon.png">
    <meta name="description"
        content="Transform any room with these DIY accent wall ideas. From bold paint colors to textured wood paneling, discover how to create a stunning focal point in your home.">
    <title>DIY Accent Wall Ideas - Home Hub</title>
    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com/3.4.16"></script>
    <script>
        tailwind.config = {
            theme: {
                extend: {
                    colors: {
                        primary: "#14B8A6",
                        secondary: "#0F766E",
                    },
                    borderRadius: {
                        none: "0px",
                        sm: "4px",
                        DEFAULT: "8px",
                        md: "12px",
                        lg: "16px",
                        xl: "20px",
                        "2xl": "24px",
                        "3xl": "32px",
                        full: "9999px",
                        button: "8px",
                    },
                },
            },
        };
    </script>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Pacifico&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <link href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/remixicon/4.6.0/remixicon.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/responsive.css">
</head>

<body class="bg-white">
    <%- include("../partials/header") %>

        <main class="py-8 bg-white">
            <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
                    <article class="lg:col-span-2">
                        <div class="bg-white">
                            <nav class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-6">
                                <a href="/" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">Home</a>
                                <span class="mx-2">></span>
                                <a href="/diy-projects" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">DIY Projects</a>
                                <span class="mx-2">></span>
                                <span class="text-gray-800">Accent Wall Ideas</span>
                            </nav>

                            <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 leading-tight">
                                DIY Accent Wall Ideas That Transform Any Room
                            </h1>

                            <div class="mb-8">
                                <img src="/images/accent-wall-ideas.webp"
                                    alt="Room with a beautiful dark blue accent wall"
                                    class="w-full h-80 object-cover rounded-lg shadow-lg" fetchpriority="high">
                            </div>

                            <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
                                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Introduction</h2>
                                <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
                                    An accent wall is one of the quickest and most cost-effective ways to change the
                                    mood of a room. Whether you want a bold pop of color or a subtle texture, there's an
                                    accent wall DIY for every skill level.
                                </p>

                                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Paint: The Classic Choice</h2>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">A simple coat of paint can be incredibly powerful.
                                    Consider these paint-based accent wall ideas:</p>
                                <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-6">
                                    <li><strong>Bold Solid Color:</strong> Choose a deep navy, forest green, or moody
                                        charcoal for drama.</li>
                                    <li><strong>Geometric Patterns:</strong> Use painter's tape to create sharp, modern
                                        triangles or stripes.</li>
                                    <li><strong>Color Blocking:</strong> Paint only the bottom half of the wall or a
                                        specific architectural feature.</li>
                                </ul>

                                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Texture and Dimension</h2>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">If you want something more than just color, add materials
                                    that give the wall some physical presence.</p>
                                <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-6">
                                    <li><strong>Board and Batten:</strong> A timeless look that adds architectural
                                        interest to any room.</li>
                                    <li><strong>Peel and Stick Wallpaper:</strong> Perfect for renters or those who want
                                        a complex pattern without the commitment.</li>
                                    <li><strong>Wood Slats:</strong> Create a modern, industrial vibe with vertical or
                                        horizontal wood slats.</li>
                                </ul>

                                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Conclusion</h2>
                                <p class="text-gray-700">
                                    Don't be afraid to experiment. If you don't like it, most accent wall treatments are
                                    easy to paint over or remove. The impact they have on your space is well worth the
                                    effort.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </article>

                    <aside class="lg:col-span-1">
                        <div class="sticky top-8 space-y-6">
                            <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6">
                                <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Design Tip</h3>
                                <p class="text-gray-600">Choose the wall that first catches your eye when you enter the
                                    room as your accent wall. Usually, this is the wall behind the bed or the sofa.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </aside>
                </div>
            </div>
        </main>

        <%- include("../partials/footer") %>
            <script src="/js/script.js"></script>
</body>

</html>